    "summary": "15 years of SAP experience in SAP PP-PI and QM, with projects in Brazil, Argentina, Col\u00f4mbia, El Salvador, United States, China, India, Germany and Portugal.\n\nSuccessful hands on projects implemented in big companies, such as Chevron, Shell, John Deere, P&H Minepro, Cameron, Jabil, ZhongDing, Modine, Arcelor Mittal and Sanofi.\n\nStrong manufacturing and quality experience, having led manufacturing cells and successfully conducted implementation of ISO programs in industries such as pharmaceutical, electronics, chemical, plastic, automotive, steel, mining, oil and gas.\n\nOver the course of 15 years of experience, I have successfully implemented the following PP-PI/QM activities:\n\u2022\tMaster data conversion; fit gap analysis, blueprint, IMG configuration, RICEF requirements, testing, user training, dress rehearsal testing, integration testing.\n\u2022\tSuccessfully configured and implemented PP with the following sub-modules: SOP, DRP, MRP, Capacity Planning and Discrete and Repetitive Manufacturing.\n\u2022\tSuccessfully configured and implemented PP-PI with the following sub-modules: SOP, MRP, Process Order, Process Planning.\n\u2022\tSuccessfully configured and implemented QM with the following sub-modules: Quality Planning, Quality Inspection, Quality Certificates, Calibration and Quality Notification.\n\n\n",
